gomodel:SYNGO_1597  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The mEPSC frequency is reduced upon hnRNP K silencing, indicating reduced pre-synaptic transmission. Note that the dendritic length, the number of dentiric branches and the number of spines is also affected.. Experimental description: All experiments were performed on dissociated hippocampal neurons prepared from **rat embryos**" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2094-7491" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4419-210X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9848-0262" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1190-4481" ;
